The displacement of the object<br><ol><li><b>Decreases</b> as it&nbsp;returns to equilibrium.</li><li><b>Reverses and increases</b>&nbsp;as it moves away from equilibrium in the opposite direction.<br></li><li><b>Decreases</b>&nbsp;as it returns to equilibrium.<br></li><li><b>Increase&nbsp;</b>as it moves away from equilibrium<b>&nbsp;towards its starting position</b><span style="font-weight: bold;">.</span></li></ol>